    "At the 0 setting, the narrative foregrounds God's compassion and patience, guiding Jonah towards an understanding and acceptance of divine will.",
    "Alignment with the \"Jonah is wrong\" perspective is evident in the portrayal of Jonah's journey from resistance to acceptance of God's plan, a transformation that underscores the central theme of the trend: the universal scope of God's mercy.",
    "Additionally, the positive depiction of Nineveh post-repentance and Jonah's eventual acknowledgment of God's love highlight the transformative and universal nature of divine mercy.",
